ECB Seeks New Liquidity Plan for Irish Banks, WSJ Says

-- B y   M i k e   M i l l a r d
-- 
2011-03-28T01:06:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-28/ecb-seeks-new-liquidity-plan-for-irish-banks-wsj-says.html
The  European Central Bank  is
devising a plan to keep troubled Irish banks afloat, the Wall
Street Journal reported, citing an unidentified euro-zone
banking official.  The facility would replace the use of Emergency Liquidity
Assistance, and offer lending to assist banks faced with short-
term emergencies, the Journal reported. The ECB declined to
comment, it said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Mike Millard at 
 mmillard2@bloomberg.net  